1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE BILL 4407 By: Blancett
4
5
6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to long-term care; creating the
Options Counseling for Long-term Care Revolving Fund;
8 stating the purpose; providing for codification;
providing an effective date; and declaring an
9 emergency.
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3002.8 of Title 56, unless there
15 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving fund
17 for the Oklahoma Department of Human Services to be designated the
18 "Options Counseling for Long-term Care Revolving Fund". The fund
19 shall be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations,
20 and shall consist of all monies received by the Oklahoma Department
21 of Human Services from state-appropriated funds, federal funds,
22 donations, grants, and contributions from any public or private
23 source and designated for the purpose set forth in this section.
24 All monies accruing to the credit of said fund are hereby
Req. No. 14271 Page 1

1 appr opriated and may be budgeted and expended by the Oklahoma
2 Department of Human Services for the purpose of providing
3 individuals, their representatives, or both, with long-term care
4 options consultation by phone or in person. Expenditures from said
5 fund shall be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer
6 against claims filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the
7 Office of Management and Enterprise Services for approval and
8 payment.
9 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
10 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
11 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
12 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
13 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
